			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">The package of 5 modules aims to train individuals on the quantitative methods of comparative efficiency measurement while also familiarising them with the broader behavioural issues of their use in Performance Management. The methods are based on linear programming and econometrics and are used to measure the productive efficiency of units transforming resources into useful outcomes. Examples of such units are hospitals, sales outlets, bank branches or police forces. The methods help identify good operating practices, most productive scale sizes, the scope for efficiency savings and technologies or policies conducive to productivity improvements. The modules will be delivered in video-supported residential weekend sessions and can be taken as stand-alone training courses or as part of an MSc or MBA qualification. This flexibility is designed to facilitate those with work or other commitments unable to attend weekly sessions or unwilling to embark on full masters degrees</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
